  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provide Clean Drinking Water for a School in India</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The rainwater harvesting program of the Barefoot College is a sustainable solution to the extreme shortage of clean drinking water sources in rural Rajasthan, India. Rains are often undependable and ground water has unhealthy levels of arsenic or fluoride, and in many areas is too saline to drink. Rainwater - as a direct source of potable water when filtered - can be collected from the rooftops of schools and stored in underground storage tanks. Communities contribute to constructing the system.</narrative>
  </description>
